  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently re-filling test cases takes quite a while, so they are re-filled manually instead.\r\n\r\nIt would be better if we could detect when they need to be refilled automatically, and even better if this was done by the CI server for us automatically on every PR. I would settle for a way to automatically only refill tests that need to be refilled though.\r\n\r\nA simple solution: include (in the filled output) a hash of the original file. Check that hash before filling, and if it hasn't changed, then refill.\r\n\r\nAnother potential solution: track filled -> filler dependencies using a Makefile or the like. Have a CI server which does not wipe out the repository between test runs, so is able to track dependencies properly using timestamps. This is a bit more fragile.\r\n\r\nThis could also make an argument for reintroducing a `master` branch: devs push PRs to `develop` without filling tests, a CI server occasionally packages a release of the `develop` branch by filling tests and pushing to `master` branch.\r\n\r\nThoughts? @axic @pirapira @winsvega @chfast ",
